Gbadebo Rhodes-Vivour, governorship candidate of the Labour Party in Lagos State has donated N15 million to shop owners whose shops were burnt at Akere Spare Parts Market, Ajegunle in the Apapa area of Lagos State. In a video shared online, the governorship candidate, who visited the scene, was filmed whispering to the man next to him. The man then announced the donation saying, “ He gave us N15 million naira.” The cheers from the crowd drowned the rest of the announcement as the excited traders lifted Rhodes-Vivour in appreciation. Credit: Twitter | JaypeeGeneral 